Source: xhotkeys
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Arnau Sanchez <arnau@ehas.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0), imagemagick
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: xhotkeys
Architecture: all
Depends: python (>= 2.3), python-gtk2, python-glade2, python-xlib
Description: Bind keys and mouse events to commands in the X-Window
 XhotKeys binds commands to hotkeys and mouse event in the X-Window
 System (so it should work on all desktop interfaces). You can 
 configure the hotkeys manually or with a little graphical GTK+ app.
